---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Icon from '../../../components/Icon.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="For Municipalities & Media - Ferienwohnungsverein Jungfrau"
  description="Factsheet, contacts, and background for municipal councillors and journalists on the short-term rental debate in the Bernese Oberland."
  langAlt="/fuer-gemeinden-medien/"
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="section page-hero hero--intro">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>For Municipalities &amp; Media</h1>
      <p>We don't deny the housing problem – but we show that there are better paths than a rigid 90-day rule.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Factsheet -->
  <section class="section section--white">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Factsheet at a Glance</h2>
      <ul class="icon-list">
        <li><Icon name="check-square" size={24} /><span><strong>Five Bödeli municipalities, five paths</strong> – not a uniform "ban wave," but different, in part already proven approaches.</span></li>
        <li><Icon name="check-square" size={24} /><span><strong>The Wilderswil model already works:</strong> 70% primary-residence quota + 5-night minimum stay, adopted with 83.5% approval. The SP subsequently withdrew its own initiative.</span></li>
        <li><Icon name="check-square" size={24} /><span><strong>Bans alone don't reliably solve housing shortages:</strong> New York's near-total Airbnb ban neither lowered rents nor increased vacancy.</span></li>
        <li><Icon name="check-square" size={24} /><span><strong>Enforcement is decisive:</strong> Even Bern's rule, adopted with 81% approval, is still not in force today; in Geneva, an analysis found nearly half of hosts violate the existing 90-day rule.</span></li>
        <li><Icon name="check-square" size={24} /><span><strong>The federal government is moving:</strong> SECO/SEM are preparing a nationwide, unified registration scheme (as of January 2025) – we support this development.</span></li>
      </ul>
      <p class="spacer-top">All figures and sources in detail: <a href="/en/sources/">Sources</a> and <a href="/en/our-proposal/">Our Proposal</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What we offer -->
  <section class="section section--subtle">
    <div class="container text-center">
      <h2>What We Offer</h2>
      <p class="lead">Active participation in workshops to develop a model that's realistic for your municipality – not obstruction, but collaboration.</p>
      <a href="/en/contact/" class="btn btn-accent">Contact</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .icon-list {
    margin-block: var(--space-3);
  }

  .icon-list li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .lead {
    max-width: 65ch;
    margin-inline: auto;
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
  }

  .center-btn {
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  .spacer-top {
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
  }

  .spacer-top-sm {
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }
</style>
